benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/bundles - Retrieve bundles for account

covered: Valid Request: Scenarios TC01, TC07, TC08 cover successful retrieval, empty result, and single bundle cases.
Query Parameters: TC02 (externalKey filter), TC03 (bundlesFilter), TC04/TC05 (audit FULL/MINIMAL), TC06 (combined parameters) cover parameterized queries and audit controls.

Error Handling and Validation: TC9 (malformed accountId), TC10 (non-existent account), TC11 (invalid audit value), TC15 (malicious input), TC21 (dependency/2xx/5xx cases), TC14 (service unavailable), TC17 (timeout), TC18 (concurrent requests), TC22 (data consistency after creation).
Authorization: TC13 (unauthorized access) tests auth failure scenario.
Regression/Compatibility: TC19 (regression for audit FULL), TC20 (backward compatibility with older clients), TC24/TC25 (input edge cases and documentation compliance).
Edge/Niche scenarios: TC07, TC08 cover no-bundle and single-bundle cases; TC16 (large data volume) hints at performance considerations, and TC22 confirms new bundle visibility.
gaps: Pagination: No explicit tests for pagination behavior when data set is large or for page/size navigation.
Caching Behavior: No tests validating caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) or cache-related behavior.
Rate Limiting: No tests validating behavior under rapid consecutive requests or throttling.
Audit/Field Coverage: While audit parameter scenarios exist, deeper validation of exact audit field structures (FULL/MINIMAL) across multiple bundles could be strengthened.
Edge case consistency: TC24/TC25 cover input edge cases but could be extended with more deterministic validation of mixed valid/invalid parameter combinations (beyond what is currently described).
recommendations: Add explicit pagination tests: verify correct page/size handling, total counts, and behavior when requesting subsequent pages with and without filters.
Add caching tests: verify presence and correctness of caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control), and behavior on conditional requests (If-None-Matter-What).
Add rate limiting tests: simulate bursts or rapid successive requests to ensure proper throttling/429 responses if applicable.
Strengthen audit field validation: include tests that assert exact audit metadata shapes for FULL and MINIMAL across multiple bundles and different account states.
Expand edge-case parameter combos: create scenarios with mixed valid/invalid parameter sequences to ensure robust input validation and graceful handling.
